The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for visual recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the training procedure of these networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The proposed methodology involves the use of matrix computations, which is a topic in both artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper includes experiments on visual segmentation, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
